cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.DB, cs.LG. 

The paper presents a data summarization algorithm for vectors in high-dimensional space, which can be used for summarizing network graphs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the application of the algorithm to network graphs, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the algorithm can be used for maintaining an approximated sum of vectors from an unbounded stream, which could place it in cs.DB (Databases) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
